node.label: Based on ISA-95 Part 1 Figure 3, Page 19, Figure 4, page 23. This view applies the ArchiMate definition of location "A location is defined as a conceptual point or extent in space." to machinery as well, since machinery occupies space. All machinery is assumed also to have a processing capacity, i.e. a node that can run control applications, including ones that are embedded.
